1. Styling: adding more bootstrap styling including a navbar with working active navbar item 2. Added search capability to filter songs. Interestingly enough angularjs would have been very easy to implement filtering
using GET in search to simplify code and since search is idempotent
user login and logout functionality. Using most of djangos default views. added styling and such
hide search bar from mobile make sure active_page works with the login page

added ability to register including forms and validation. All fields are required for now. Auto login after successful registration. Email verification will happen later (need to setup my email server)
also going with green buttons , the green and grey works well IMO
added missing migration moved Register to a more appropriate template path

added unique constraint on name, alas it is not case insensitive yet due to postgres. Added new and delete buttons. Added table to show songs with new view edit delete buttons. Finally, added FormHelper to the new and edit forms to allow for crispy form token
update register form to use form helper
jump directly to song detail view if search yields one result
add new artist, edit existing artists in the song list
Minor refactoring and changing of UI - instead of allowing users to edit / add artists from the song list i created a new artist list

biggest change - comments! simple commenting system to allow users to add comments to a song.

allow a user to delete their own comments.
